        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Create a new Zend_Soap_Client_* that can handle <xsd:import>.\n\n{code}<definitions ...>\n    <types>\n        <xsd:schema>\n            <xsd:import namespace=\"...\" schemaLocation=\"http:\/\/www.example.com\/service?xsd=1\">\n        <\/xsd:schema>\n    <\/types>\n    ...\n<\/definitons>{code}\n\n{code:title=http:\/\/www.example.com\/service?xsd=1}<xs:schema version=\"1.0\" targetNamespace=\"http:\/\/jaxb.dev.java.net\/array\">\n    <xs:complexType name=\"intArray\" final=\"#all\">\n        <xs:sequence>\n            <xs:element name=\"item\" type=\"xs:int\" minOccurs=\"0\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\" nillable=\"true\"\/>\n        <\/xs:sequence>\n    <\/xs:complexType>\n<\/xs:schema>{code}\n\nSoapClient seems to be unable to handle <xsd:import> and is causing an endless loop.\n\nWorkaround:\n* download WSDL and XSD files\n* change schemaLocation-URLs to local files\n* initialize SoapClient with modified WSDL file\n\nWorks fine, but I don't know whether this is the best way to solve this problem."
